function xorGame(nums) {
    let xorSum = 0;
    for (let num of nums) {
        xorSum ^= num;
    }
    return xorSum === 0 || nums.length % 2 === 0;
}
```

    The algorithm first calculates the bitwise XOR of all elements in the array. Then, it checks if the XOR of all elements is zero or if the total number of elements in the array is even.

If the bitwise XOR of all elements is zero, Alice wins because the game condition is already satisfied and it is her turn. If the total number of elements in the array is even, Alice wins because she can always force a situation where the bitwise XOR of the remaining elements is non-zero when it is Bob's turn to play. In all other cases, Alice will lose, and the function returns false.

